Boy On A String - Jars Of Clay

All Guitars EABEBE Tuning (capo 3)

That stuff underneath the TAB is the length of each note.  'e' is an
eighth note, 's' is a sixteenth note, 'e.' is a doted eighth note, and
so on.  The '/' between two notes means that they are tied.  An underlined
letter is a rest.  The TAB is just standard TAB.

